Bash Color codes: \[\033[COLORm\]
Here are the values for foreground colors:

Black : 30 \[\033[30m\] Bold \[\033[1;30m\]
Blue  : 34 \[\033[34m\] Bold \[\033[1;34m\]
Cyan  : 36 \[\033[36m\] Bold \[\033[1;36m\]
Green : 32 \[\033[32m\] Bold \[\033[1;32m\]
Purple: 35 \[\033[35m\] Bold \[\033[1;35m\]
Red   : 31 \[\033[31m\] Bold \[\033[1;31m\]
White : 37 \[\033[37m\] Bold \[\033[1;37m\]
Yellow: 33 \[\033[33m\] Bold \[\033[1;33m\]

Here are the values for background colors: (No attribute allowed)

Black background : 40 \[\033[40m\]
Blue background  : 44 \[\033[44m\]
Cyan background  : 46 \[\033[46m\]
Green background : 42 \[\033[42m\]
Purple background: 45 \[\033[45m\]
Red background   : 41 \[\033[41m\]
White background : 47 \[\033[47m\]
Yellow background: 43 \[\033[43m\]

reset or stop coloring:

\[\033[00m\]

And lastly a simple working prompt(default=PS1 save the current prompt to enable revert):
default=PS1
PS1='\[\033[1;31m\]\u\[\033[1;37m\]@\[\033[1;31m\]\h\[\033[1;36m\][\[\033[1;37m\]\w\[\033[1;36m\]]\[\033[37m\]: '
